SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 708
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Battle Ground
Academy Wildcats, 2025 TSSAA Division II-AA
state football champions.
WHEREAS, the members of this legislative body are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school teams that, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, the Battle Ground Academy (BGA) Wildcats achieved an extraordinary level
of success during the 2025 season, winning the coveted TSSAA Division II-AA state football
championship to claim their first state title in twenty-two years; and
WHEREAS, in the state playoffs, Battle Ground Academy defeated three strong
opponents to reach the championship game; and
WHEREAS, BGA matched up against Franklin Road Academy (FRA) in the title tilt, and
senior quarterback Kaedyn Marable led the way to victory with seven total touchdowns, tying a
state championship record; and
WHEREAS, other key performers included wide receiver Max Curry who scored three
touchdowns and wide receiver Maddox Porter who scored one touchdown; and
WHEREAS, the Wildcats trounced FRA 61-27 to claim the crown of state champions
and bring home the gold; and
WHEREAS, state championships are achieved only through hard work, dedication, and
the ability to work together as a team and excel with a cooperative spirit; the BGA Wildcats
exhibited each of these rare qualities during their championship season; and
WHEREAS, the football players of Battle Ground Academy epitomize all that is good in
today's student athletes, as they have achieved the highest level of success on the field while
showing the highest degree of character both on and off the field; they inspired their fellow
SJR0708
013132
